rComments: A real gem! Loved the course and he did a good job of introducing the Middle East- a land that is so complicated and can be difficult to understand.

Despite conservative layout of course, he admits it to be so because it's a good introductory method. 2 exams and 1 essay, all of which are pretty easy if you do the readings and attend most lectures. Lecs are interesting, despite slightly rapid pace. Very knowledgable man, kind of cute how he's passionate about MENA history. Unbiased.
